---
When logging in this codebase:
- Always use structlog, never print() or stdlib logging directly
- Every logger must be bound with context before use:
    poller: bind city="Ottawa" and component="poller"
    API:    bind path, method, request_id
- Log level conventions:
    DEBUG:   raw API response bodies only
    INFO:    reading stored, event fired, request completed
    WARNING: poll failed after retries — must include city (str),
             http_status (int|None), attempt_count (int), error_msg (str)
    ERROR:   DB connection failure, unhandled exception
- A duplicate reading is NOT an error — log at INFO with duplicate=True
- Every WARNING for a failed poll must include exactly these fields:
  city, http_status, attempt_count, error_msg. No exceptions.
